column.name: content
column.value:
Severity
The impact on the customer's systems and end-users.

S6 Showstopper
Stops further use of the product or service.
S5 Critical
Security issue, crash or data loss.
S4 Major
Functionality issue with a major impact.
S3 Medium
Functionality issue with a medium impact.
S2 Minor
Functionality issue with a minor impact.
S1 Trivial
Cosmetic issue.
S0 Enhancement
New Feature Request.

column.name: content
column.value:
Urgency
Internal prioritization of tickets. Order in which to resolve tickets.

U5 Immediate To be resolved immediately.
U4 Urgent To be resolved in the next minor release.
U3 High To be resolved in the next major release.
U2 Medium To be resolved in the next major release.
U1 Low To be resolved in the next major release.

column.name: content
column.value:
Status
The current status of the issue.

New Issue has just been submitted by the customer.
Open Support is processing the issue.
In Progress Issue is being resolved by the support.
More Info Required More information is required from the customer.
By Design The issue reported by the customer is by design and not an error.
Won't Implement The issue reported by the customer will not be implemented.
Won't Fix The issue reported by the customer will not be fixed.
Resolved
Issue has been resolved by support, but has not been verified by customer.
Closed
Issue has been closed.

column.name: content
column.value:
Severity
The impact on the customer's systems and end-users.

S6 Showstopper
Stops further use of the product or service.
S5 Critical
Security issue, crash or data loss.
S4 Major
Functionality issue with a major impact.
S3 Medium
Functionality issue with a medium impact.
S2 Minor
Functionality issue with a minor impact.
S1 Trivial
Cosmetic issue.
S0 Enhancement
New Feature Request.

column.name: content
column.value:
Urgency
Internal prioritization of tickets. Order in which to resolve tickets.

U5 Immediate To be resolved immediately.
U4 Urgent To be resolved in the next minor release.
U3 High To be resolved in the next major release.
U2 Medium To be resolved in the next major release.
U1 Low To be resolved in the next major release.

column.name: content
column.value:
Status
The current status of the issue.

New Issue has just been submitted by the customer.
Open Support is processing the issue.
In Progress Issue is being resolved by the support.
More Info Required More information is required from the customer.
By Design The issue reported by the customer is by design and not an error.
Won't Implement The issue reported by the customer will not be implemented.
Won't Fix The issue reported by the customer will not be fixed.
Resolved
Issue has been resolved by support, but has not been verified by customer.
Closed
Issue has been closed.
